Participants requiring accomodation will have to mention this while registering online. You will be put up in hostels inside the campus. Transportation however will not be provided.

While we will be providing all sound system requirements (amplifiers, mics, 5 piece drum kit, audio cables) participants will have to bring their own instruments.

3. When do we have to reach IITM? 
Participants have to ensure that they reach IITM by 9am. However for it is recommended that you come on Day 1 itself for a wholesome Saarang experience. 

4. Do we need to get our college ids? 
Yes. Valid college ids are mandatory for all events except Decibels.

5.  Can a participant be a part of more than one band in the same event? 
No. Participants are allowed to represent only one band per event

fields.event_format:
Event Format and Rules

Participants with B-high or higher grades in their respective fields in the AIR are not allowed to participate as the competition is aimed at amateurs and semi-professionals. 

Prelims:-

  • Light music solo vocals event.
  • This is an open event for all college students.
  • Performances should be in Indian languages only. Presence of considerable foreign language might lead to disqualification, based on the judge’s discretion.
  • Contestants will be registered on the spot. A Saarang ID is a MUST for anyone to participate in this event. Only registered participants will be allowed to perform. Registrations will start at the hospitality desk ONE HOUR prior to the beginning of the event. A valid college ID card is necessary for registration.
  • Event would be organized in a three level fashion, i.e. prelims , semi- finals and finals.
  • Time given per contestant- 3:30 mins + 30 secs.
  • One accompaniment (instrument)/MIDI backing track, is allowed.
  • In case of the accompaniment being an MIDI track, it has to be submitted to the event coordinators before the event starts. Allowance of the MIDI track is up to the event coordinator’s discretion.
  • Strictly no extra time would be given on stage; all the tuning and bending of instruments should be done before handed.
  • Instruments will not be provided by us.
  • Metronome is not allowed.
  • Shruti box is permitted. You are expected to bring your own.
  • In case of any discrepancy the event organiser’s OR judge’s decision would be final and binding

 

.

Semi-Finals:-

 

  • ONLY 16-20 participants will be selected from the prelims for the semifinals.
  • Participants are allowed to sing the same song that they performed for the prelims.
  • Rest of the rules remain the same as that of prelims.

 

Finals:-

 

  • ONLY 8-10 participants will be selected.
  • The participant will be asked to prepare 3 types of Indian language songs, which will be intimated right after semi-finals.

2 rounds of registration:

For Pre-Registration:

  • Teams are required to send the following.
  • YouTube link of a video of the team’s performance sent in by 30th November.
  • Details about the team including previous performances/any achievements should be mailed to choreo@saarang.org. before the deadline.

? The competition is divided into two categories - Theme and Non-Theme. Each category will be judged separately.

fields.event_format:
Classical Dance Solo:

  • You can perform in any Indian classical dance form [we'd love to see bharatnatyam, kuchipudi, odissi, mohiniyattam and others]. However there are no separate judging categories for the different forms.
  • Preliminary Round:

The participant has to perform a prepared piece (varnam or thillana) in any dance form. (Time limit : 5+2 mins) Participant need not wear the formal dance costumes but can wear any traditional classical dance wear (dance sari or kurta with dupatta for girls and panchakacham for guys). There will be a small weightage for costumes.

  • Final Round: The finals will comprise of the following two rounds :

Round 1 :  The participants who are short-listed for the finals, will be given two themes once the preliminary round is over. They can choose anyone of the given themes, prepare their own choreography for the same and dance for the chosen theme to only semi classical instrumental music. (Time limit : 3+1) Round 2 : In this round, the participant will be interacting with the judges. The participant may be asked to do abhinaya or anything similar, given by the judges and judged accordingly. (Time limit : 4+2 mins) The participants have to perform with proper classical dance costume in the finals. There will be weightage for the costumes in the final round. The songs should be strictly classical [except for the finals, where you will have to perform for a semi classical instrumental piece]. We do not appreciate film music. Please bring your cassettes or CDs and a pendrive with the dance music in MP3 format (in case the CDs or cassettes don’t work). [Only the player will be provided by us]

Classical Dance Group :

  • A group can perform any prepared piece of dance. The performance should strictly be in classical dance forms only.
  • Time limit for each group is 6+2 minutes. Performance of different dance forms within the same group is permitted.
  • Minimum number of participants per group is 2 and maximum number of participants per group is 8 along with a maximum of 2 backstage helpers. Atleast 2 people should be on stage at any given time.
  • Participants from different colleges can form a group to participate.
  • The songs should be strictly classical. We do not appreciate film music. Please bring your cassettes or CDs and a pendrive with the dance music in MP3 format (in case the CDs or cassettes do not work). [Only the player will be provided by us]

    Classical Music Vocals

    • Artistes with B-high or higher grades in their respective fields in the AIR are not allowed to participate as this competition is meant for amateurs and semi-professionals.
    • Eligibility : Class 9 and above.

     

     

    • Hindustani and Carnatic will be judged together.
    • We will make available an electronic sruthi box. No other instruments will be made available.
    • Judges’ decision shall be final in all respects and should be accepted without question.

    Prelims

    • Time limit : 6 mins (this might be reduced if there are too many participants) The judges may also opt to make it shorter if they feel that they have heard as much as is required for judging.
    • Carnatic Participants have to be prepared with 3 ‘kritis’ out of which you may be asked to sing any one. In general, varnams, swarajathis and geethams are not accepted as kritis, but there are a few exceptions (e.g. Shyama Shatri\'s swarajathis).  All participants are strongly encouraged to sing one or more of the following: ragam, neraval, kalpana swarams. You need not sing all the three to qualify for the finals.
    • We also advise you against singing lighter raagams like Revathi, Bhaagyashree and Shivaranjini. You are encouraged to sing gana/rakti raagams.
    • Hindustani Participants have to sing one raga, and it may contain one or two songs. Dhrupads, Khayals and Taranas are allowed. Thumris, Tappas, Bhajans and Ghazals will not be allowed. If in doubt, send a mail to one of the coordinators to confirm that the song you are preparing will be accepted. The performance must ordinarily contain at least two of the following: Anibaddh Alaap, Bol Alaap, Sargam and Taans. In other words, you will have to demonstrate the ability to improvise on the spot. You will be allowed to use an electronic Tabla but you will be required to switch off the electronic display of the taal cycle. In other words, you will have to demonstrate the ability to read the bol of the Tabla. Alternatively, you may be accompanied by one person on the Tabla. No non-percussion accompaniment is allowed.

    Finals


    • If you qualify for the finals, you will have to give a list of 5 kritis in different ragas. You may not sing the same raga that you sang in the prelims. No changes to the list would be encouraged once you submit it. All finalists are assumed to be competent enough to sing raagam and kalpana swarams in each of the 5 kritis, and neraval in most of the kritis. The finalists may be asked by the judges to move ahead and sing neraval/kalpana swarams. The judges may impose different types of creative restrictions to evaluate your talent. All of this is left to the judges' discretion. Since the aim of this round is to decide a winner and most of the rules are dictated by the judges, there is no strict limit on the time allotted, though we expect that a participant will not take more than 20 min.
    • Hindustani A list of 3 ragas must be submitted before the start of the finals. Please note that the list should not have the raga you rendered in the prelims. No changes to the list would be encouraged once you submit it. The participant will be assumed competent enough to render a full performance in all the ragas. There are no limitations on the number of songs you sing, but your performance will have to encompass at least two layas. The judges may ask you to move ahead and sing sargam/tans. They might impose all sorts of creative restrictions; prescribe the bol to use for the tans etc. All of this is left to the judges' discretion. Since the aim of this round is to decide a winner and as most of the rules are dictated by the judges, there is no strict limit on the time allotted, though we expect that a participant will not take more than 20 min.

      Classical Music Instrumental( Non- Percussion)

      • Artistes with B-high or higher grades in their respective fields in the AIR are not allowed to participate as this competition is meant for amateurs and semi-professionals.
      • Eligibility : Class 9 and above.
      • Hindustani and Carnatic will be judged together.

       

      • All instruments will be judged together.
      • One person can participate only once.
      • Regarding the pieces that can be played, the same rules as those for vocal prelims apply.
      • Time limit: 6 minutes, though this might change depending on the number of participants.

       

      • We will make available an electronic shruthi box. No other instruments will be made available.
      • Judges' decision shall be final in all respects and should be accepted without question.

      Classical Music Instrumental (Percussion)

      • Artistes with B-high or higher grades in their respective fields in the AIR are not allowed to participate as this competition is meant for amateurs and semi-professionals.
      • Eligibility : Class 9 and above.
      • Hindustani and Carnatic will be judged together.

       

      • Electronic instruments are not allowed.
      • The participants will be required to give a list of three talams in which they are prepared to play a thani avarthanam or a solo piece.
      • The judges may ask them to play one more tala from the list provided. Participants may also be required to recite the korvais or other pieces played on judges' demand.
      • Participants may play in Carnatic/Hindustani style. However, they will not be judged separately.
      • Time limit: 6 minutes, though this might change depending on the number of participants. Please stick to the time limit.
      • Any sort of assistance to aid rhythm like music, rhythm clocks etc. are not allowed.

       

      • We will make available an electronic shruthi box. No other instruments will be made available.
      • Judges' decision shall be final in all respects and should be accepted without question.

Come, participate, bring out the designer in you!

Vocals, instruments, and some crazy energy. The only thing missing from Saarang was

some music to get the crowd grooving and partying. Here's your chance to pump up the

party with DJukebox - our all new and absolutely insane DJing event for school and

college DJs!

fields.about:
“Movies will make you famous; Television will make you rich; But theatre will make you good.”

-Terrence Mann

Nuff said? We don’t think so! This year prepare yourself to tear up, sniffle, and laugh out loud as Saarang Dramatics returns. 

The stage is set. We just have to turn the lights on.
fields.name: dramatics
fields.event_format:
• Teams can be of any size.
  • Participants will have to carry ID cards to register.
  • There will be two rounds of shortlisting.

Disclaimer: Rules are subject to change without prior notice. Teams will be informed of the changes.

fields.about:
"A picture can tell a thousand words, but a few words can change its story."

If you can move crowds like Mark Antony or amuse them like Russell Peters, all you need to do is grab the Saarang mic! Enthrall the audience, make them speechless and nothing can be an obstacle between you and glory. An individual event, thou shall be thine only company!
fields.name: eloc

• Each participant is given 3 + 0.5 minutes.
  • Limited entries on the basis of first come first serve.

fields.about:
Are you the ones that are bored of long tales and NEVER- ENDING sagas?

Do you believe in the adage, "Better one word too few than one too many"?

                        Well, tell us again why less is better in our Flash Fiction event held for passionate writers of few words.  To participate in the flash fiction, like our facebook page ‘Saarang Writing Awards’’ and keep an eye out for updates all of December!
fields.name: flashfiction
fields.event_format:
• Pre-Saarang Online event.

  • Every week, in the month preceding Saarang, writing prompts and cues are announced in the SWA Facebook page.

  • There is a word limit of 70 words, and the entries are to be sent in as comments in the same thread as the announcement of the prompt.

  • The best 3 entries from each week will be selected by a notable judge.

  • Age limit: 16-25.

fields.oneliner: For young writers of  few words but many riddles and meanings.

fields.FAQs:
Where will the prompts be put up?

On the Saarang 2014 Facebook page. (The link to the facebook page should be given here.)

Can I send more than one short entry?

No. One entry per person for a prompt.

Can I send entries for more than one prompt?

Yes.

fields.about:
Saarang India is a comprehensive (really long + indepth) General Knowledge test on everything India from Aaryabhata to Zenana, we've got Dhoom, Dhadaka, Cool Patakas, Rajinikanth, Rasgullas and everything in between!

Put on your thinking turbans, and take part in this exhilarating journey across the warp and weft of this beautiful ancient, dynamic, definition defying, enigmatic  land we call home. Entertainment Guaranteed. Prizes too!

Laddu tinna aasai aa? No prior quizzing experience necessary. Jugaad out the answer with help from fundaes on screen.

Experience quizzing, IITM style. Best kaluri quiz klub in Indi-yeah!

Rules:
Teams of upto 3
Cross College Teams allowed
Eklavya/Akeyla/lone wolf teams allowed
Top 8 teams make it to finals after the prelims

Do setting for Pen. Answer Sheets will be provided by us.

Encourage friends to participate. Pliss to spread word. They Enjoy, You Enjoy, We enjaay.
fields.name: indiaquiz
fields.registration_info:
No pre-registration required. Simply turn up for the event and enjoy yourself!

Unless you absolutely must register. In which case just email Anand.
fields.event_format:
Written prelims. 50 questions. Rock, Paper, Scissors to break ties.

The top 8 teams from the prelims will qualify for the finals.
fields.oneliner: Saarang is India, India is Saarang
fields.prizes:
Cash Prizes:

1st prize: Rs 4500/-

2nd prize: Rs 3000/-

3rd prize: Rs 1500/-

Exotic Chocolates or Cadbury DairyMilk (depending on budget) for

Most Postmodern Desi Team name
Most Pseud Answer 1 2 3
Most Paavum quizzer
Most Outraged junta 1 2 3

Best Pun
Most desi dressed
Best Arnab Goswami impression
Best usage of 'Thirukural quote' while putting funda.
fields.FAQs:
1. Do we have to pre-register?

Registrations on the spot! Pen is mandatory. Elephant optional. 

2. Are there any prerequisites?

An open mind and lots of enthu required. Basic general knowledge and ability to put n-pseud may come in handy. 

3. What kind of questions can we expect?

All kinds of questions! There are fun visual connects, buzzer rounds,  and a whole array of new theme rounds. Go through teaser Questions on the IIT Madras Quiz Club facebook page.

4. I don't know much about India. I'm a General Quizzer. Should I take part?

Absolutely. There is a little bit of India in everything. We will try our best to nudge you gently to discover facts about India you probably didn't know before.

5. Forever Alone. May I take part?

D'oh Totally! On the spot swayamwar for those needing partners or pens. Anti-social? Akeyla also okay!

6. Wait a minute. I was at Litsoc India. How long will the finals be?

It will be a very long quiz. Length ofcourse doesn't matter does it. It's what you do with it. Saarang India Quiz endeavours to be a comprehensive test of knowledge.

7. Will you ask Tam-max Questions?

Ans 1: (tamizhaaa?) Absolutely machi!

Ans 2: (Chapatti? Rotti? Butter Nan? Parotta even) No No ofcourse naat. India Quiz believes in Unity in Diversity. It will be a well balanced quiz about everything India. A little bit for everybody. Bollywood or Bhojpuri.    

8. What is the age difference between Vikram and Anand?

5 years

9. Is Vikram Venkat single?

The question on everyone's lips.

10. Does Anand Aiyer dye his hair black?

His hair is still black, believe it or not. Magic Brahmi oil is the secret we believe.

fields.about:
The longest one minute is the last of a lecture, the shortest, the last in an exam. But, the most exciting is the one in JAM.

If pointing out flaws is your forte and if you consider plagiarism, grammatical errors, gesticulation, jump the gun, stammers, change of pace and filler words to be the Seven Deadly Sins, nothing can stop you from buzzing your opponent to punishment! Being an individual event, you are solely responsible for your actions.
fields.name: jam
fields.event_format:
1. Eight legged freaks: There are 8-10 JAMmers on stage at a time. For each topic they are given, the clock will start when a chosen speaker starts speaking.
  2. Train of thought: Participants have to speak continuously, without repetition, without grammatical errors, without slurring, without stammering, (I'd be buzzed right about now, for the repeated use of "without") without pausing, without digressing, without beating around the bush, and sustain all this for as long as possible.
  3. To stop train, pull chain: Any participant can take the mic from the current speaker and earn extra points, by buzzing, and raising a valid objection. Points are docked for wrong interruptions.
  4. Time is money: The longer you speak for, the more points you get. Each round lasts for one minute of cumulative time.
  5. Jest in the nick of time: Points are also awarded arbitrarily by the JAM moderator for humour. So, make him laugh and he will make you smile.

fields.about: Make the floor burn as you wordlessly communicate every thought and move to your partner. Let the sparks fly with even the most subtle glance. At Just Duet, it is all about the chemistry and the sync as couples perform on the Saarang platform. Watch the couples battle it out, watch as the music comes alive. Watch dance rule the stage.
fields.name: justduet
fields.registration_info:

Lend you ears to the riveting lectures by remarkable personalities from Cinema, Literature, Arts and Civil Society.

Saarang Demonstrations bring you astonishing performances by highly acclaimed artists. Get ready to witness the entralling performances this Saarang 2014.

fields.about:
One of the most competitive college quizzes in the country, the Saarang lone wolf has a rich heritage. Battle it out among a pack of hungry cubs and fight your way to the top, for only the best survives! 

Do you have it in you to survive an entire night of quizzing? Under the starry skies in the Open Air Theatre of IIT Madras, be a part of the event that crowns the king of college quizzing.

(That’s not exactly Out-of-the-Box, but you get the point!) So if you have wit or a taste for smart humor, make sure you're there!
fields.name: madads
fields.event_format:
• Teams consisting of a maximum of 7 members
  • Time on stage: 6+1 minutes. After 6 minutes, a buzzer/bell will be rung
  • Teams are allowed to use minimalistic props and costumes. But they will have to be brought by the team. Basic props will be provided. (3 chairs and 1 table)

fields.FAQs:
1. How do you register for the event?

It's an Onsite registration event. Make sure you're there!

2. Is there any restriction on the number of entries/teams per college?

No, there is no restriction on the number of teams per college.

3. Can a team have students from different colleges?

Yes, a team can comprise of students from different colleges. But they should all carry with themselves a valid ID card indicating that they belong to a particular college.

Yes, the teams are allowed to use props and costumes for Mad-Ads. However it is recommended to go with minimalistic props, as per the concept of this event. Basic props (3 Chairs and 1 Table) will be provided by the coordinators.

fields.about:
We invite you to Panache- The Fashion Fiesta at Saarang 2014!

 

Do you sometimes wish you could dress the world and make them look fashionable? Do you think you have an unmatched sense of style and panache? Then come this Saarang, and show everyone your very own to-die-for creations! Think out-of-the-box, get high on creativity and fascinate your audience with your oomph factor.

 

Prize money and lots of exciting vouchers to be won!  

 

Contact:

Smita Mujumdar (+91 8939 570 987)

Rituja Saha (+91 9840 083 395)

Ankit Jain (+91 9043 807 215)

 

Email - panache@saarang.org
fields.name: panache
fields.registration_info:
Registration - Pre-registered

 

Last date for registration: 2nd December, 2013

 

Last date for submission for elimination round: 15th December, 2013
fields.event_format:
Structure:

The competition would comprise of an elimination round and two stage rounds. Both the stage rounds will be theme based wherein the teams have to design their costumes/outfits according to the common theme.

 

Elimination Procedure:

The designers will have to mail a soft copy of their designs for the stage rounds along with the portfolios [with photo ID] of all the models walking the ramp to panache@saarang.org. The elimination round would be based on this. It is to be noted that the design submitted during this round would only be allowed for the stage rounds. Thus, the designs for both the rounds have to be sent.
fields.FAQs:
Rules and Regulations:

 

1. Panache is open to college students only.

 

2. There can be more than one team from a respective college or even crossover teams can be formed.

 

3. All the members of a team must have a valid college ID card.

 

4. Vulgarity of any kind would lead to disqualification of the team. It is strongly advised

that the team consult the organizers if the team feels that any stunt or costume design can be deemed as vulgar. The decision of the organizers would be final in any kind of resulting dispute.

 

5. Team Size: Maximum 15 members; models - 8-10, designers - 1-4.

 

6. Every team is required to represent all body types in their designs and presentation.

 

7. Stage time: 6+2 minutes; empty stage to empty stage. Each team is responsible for clearing the stage once their performance is over. At the end of all performances, each team will be given 3-5 minutes to interact with judges.

 

8. Teams are to inform the organizers of any kind of props they plan to use during the event. Use of water, fire, pets, animal skin or any hazardous materials are not allowed. Teams are instructed to consult with the organizers before using any such material.

 

9. Teams are instructed to send in their song tracks/music ten days prior to the event.

 

10. Any lighting requirements are to be informed at least two weeks before the event, any last minute requirements will not be entertained.

 

11. There must no branding on clothes.

 

12. The decision of the judges will be final and cannot be questioned.

country. Fame, glory, fans, and most importantly a celebration of your music - watch it

all work on your accord at Powerchords. It's your turn to strike a chord.

fields.about: Saarang Roadshows is an event which aims to bring into limelight the unsung, august and diverse art forms of India and take them closer to the young generation. This is an event which aims to take the performances to the people by having the performances on the road, in the midst of plebs. The event consists of exhibitions of diverse art forms from various parts of the country, performed for the love of the art by people who love the art. It brings into Saarang folk and tradition from different parts of the country. It emphatically exhibits the diversity present in our nation.It is an eye catcher and keeps the fun and frolic going on throughout saarang. Over the last two years Saarang roadshows have organised a wide range of art forms and folkshows  from all parts of India including Manipur, Karnataka and Kerala.
fields.name: roadshows

fields.about:
Once upon a time, Hercules, son of Jupiter, was sent on a quest. It was one of the twelve quests that he would carry out, to achieve atonement for his sins. He had to find the legendary golden apples that promised immortality from the Garden of the Hesperides. The demigod traversed through mountains and seas, through hot and cold. He waged numerous battles with humans and demons alike.

Whether he found it or not, it doesn't matter, since you have your own list of crazy items to collect at Saarang! Participate in Scavenger Hunt and you'll find yourself running around, going to the weirdest places, using all your quirky thinking. And if you succeed in collecting them all, you shall be rewarded!

  • Event starts off at 10:00 am on Day 2

fields.about: A perennial favourite, Scrabble at Saarang represents the popular board game played at the highest levels of college competition. Think you have a large vocabulary? Aree you familiar with AA and EUOI. Can you void your rack and come up with QUIXOTRY on a triple triple? Vowel dump to get EUOUAES? Do a hat-trick of bingos? But let's dial it down. Do you have a pen, a friend? Can you spell? Come  battle it out for Scrabble glory. May the Q be with U!
fields.name: scrabble
fields.event_format:
There will be a written prelims where participants fill in the best possible moves for a number of  provided grids. 8 finalists will play a number of games. Teams of two, but lone wolves are welcome.* Games will last 20 minutes. The dictionary followed will be CSW12.

 

*Not actual lone canis lupus specimens, but human individuals who would like to participate solo.

fields.about:
While you’re sitting alone on a bench by the edge of a pond, or when you’re sitting on the last bench

of your class looking at the graffiti on your desk, the thing in common is that your eyes are open but

they don’t see anything. While you gaze into that nothingness, your mind indulges itself into that

visual stream, floating, without complaining. It is through this poetic beauty of images that we’re

able to connect to each other in the ‘man-made’ art, cinema. That is what makes it natural; that is

the irony of it. How else would have Sam Mendes told us about the plastic cover that wanted to play

with Ricky, how else would we have known what Ben was feeling in the ‘Sound of Silence’? Here, at

Saarang, we wish to relive this dream again. And you are the creators of this dream world.

Let the magic happen!
fields.name: sfm
fields.event_format:
Event Format and Rules:

1. There is no particular theme. Duration of the short films should neither be more than 15

minutes & nor be less than 5 minutes.

2. Films of all languages (including English) should be accompanied with English subtitles.

3. The participants will have to submit their entries by mailing their film’s link on YouTube or

any other web portal, to shortfilm@saarang.org

4. You may use any video camera you deem suitable for shooting the movie. However, we

strongly discourage low-resolution cameras, including webcams and mobile-phone cameras.

5. The shortlisted teams will be asked to come to Saarang where their films will be screened.

Accommodation will be provided for the shortlisted teams.

6. Obscenity (at the discretion of the judges) of any kind is not allowed and will lead

to immediate disqualification. Please avoid photo slideshows, remixes, spoofs and

advertisements. Plagiarism is strictly prohibited. Sound track can be borrowed, but with due

credit.

7. Time Limit should be followed. Participants will be heavily penalized by judges in case of

exceeding the time limit.

8. The decision of the judges will be final and binding.
fields.FAQs:
1. Is registration required for this event?

Yes.

2. How should we submit our entries?

Mail your short film’s YouTube link or any such web portal to shortfilm@saarang.org

fields.about:

Simple. Delight the audience and the judges and walk away with prizes. Shipwreck is the place to be. Another individual event - you're on your own here.
fields.name: shipwreck

fields.about: Freedom is exhilarating. Freedom to dance in your style brings out the best in you. So impress us with your bollywood jhatkas or your Jabbawockeeez style or just be yourself. Dance like nobody is watching and take the prize away. What other way to throw your inhibitions to the air and set your soul free than freestyle? No second thoughts. Just dance.

5. No fire, water and heavy objects should be used on stage. No props are allowed.
6. No indecency will be tolerated on stage. 
7.Judges and coordinators decisions shall be final and binding. There shall be no arguments in this regard.
fields.oneliner: The event where dance as an expression of one’s soul takes over everything else. Watch as any and every form of dance sweeps the stage in a myriad of emotions and styles.

fields.FAQs:
The rules and format are as follows:

1. SpellB will be a three-level event, consisting of a written preliminary, a written semi-
final and an oral final round.

2. It is open to both school and college students. The preliminary rounds will be separate,

while the semis onwards will be held combined for both school and college students.

3. The preliminary rounds will be written tests having 40 words, which are pronounced by

the pronouncer, while the meaning of the word, and a sentence (without the actual word)

will be displayed on the screen and the participants write down the pronounced word on

the answer sheet. This round will include hidden tiebreakers i.e. some of the words will

be given additional weightage in case of a tie.

4. Semi-finalists will be intimated through phone and/or email.

5. The semi-final will be a written test common to both school and college participants. It

will consist of 25 words and the format is the same as the prelims. Again, finalists will be

intimated.

6. The final will be oral and knockout; participants will be eliminated if they spell out a

word wrongly.

7. The Oxford Dictionary will serve as a reference for British English and it is to be noted

that American spellings will NOT be allowed.

8. An audience round will be held, where relatively simple words will be pronounced in

reverse. Prizes are assured for this round.

9. The co-ordinators’ decision is final and binding.

fields.about:
While you’re sitting alone on a bench by the edge of a pond, or when you’re sitting on the last bench

of your class looking at the graffiti on your desk, the thing in common is that your eyes are open but

they don’t see anything. While you gaze into that nothingness, your mind indulges itself into that

visual stream, floating, without complaining. It is through this poetic beauty of images that we’re

able to connect to each other in the ‘man-made’ art, cinema. That is what makes it natural; that is

the irony of it. How else would have Sam Mendes told us about the plastic cover that wanted to play

with Ricky, how else would we have known what Ben was feeling in the ‘Sound of Silence’? Here, at

Saarang, we wish to relive this dream again. And you are the creators of this dream world.

Let the magic happen!

fields.description:
Rock Show:

Architects are a 4-piece English band from Brighton. Known as Unharmonic at the time of their formation in 2004, the band changed their name to Counting the Days, before finally adopting their current name. Primarily a metal-core band, Architects are also proficient in progressive metal, mathcore and post-hardcore genres.

The past decade of their existence saw the release of 5 albums and one split up with Dead Swans, with their sixth album recently released. They are all set to release a film – One Hundred Days: The Story of Architects Almost World Tour- about the 100 day tour for which funding was completely raised from loyal fans. The band has played in some of the biggest festivals in the world, like Download, Summer Breeze, Resurrection Fest, Grasspop Metal Meeting, Sonisphere Festival, and Hellfest, each boasting five-figure audiences, and has toured in some of the most coveted tours like the Vans Wraped Tour, with some of the biggest names in the metal world like Deftones, August Burns Red, Enter Shikari, Whitechapel, and All That Remains, to name but a few.

Referred to as "pumped with both controlled rage and unhindered heart, accessible and ambitious, aggressive and beautiful", Architects have performed at various places all over the world, including America, Canada, Germany, England, Malaysia, Philippines and other countries of Europe, Australia and Asia, making the crowd go berserk in every performance. This January, Architects will be enthralling the Indian audience for the first ever time, headlining the Saarang 2014 Rockshow. This will be one great show for not just metal lovers, but for anyone who appreciate some good music!

Classical Night:

The prodigal Violin duo, fondly addressed as Ganesh-Kumaresh, took to the violin like a fish to water. Having delivered over a hundred performances before the tender age of ten, they moved on from strength to strength, emerging as one of the finest violinists of today. Popularly recognized for their refreshingly entertaining and interactive concerts, Ganesh-Kumaresh will feature in Classical Night, Saarang 2014 - treating the audience to an evening of pure delight and magic.

Sonal Mansingh, a recipient of Padma Vibhushan, is one of the most eminent Odissi dancers of today, apart from being proficient in various other dance forms. Having started her dancing career at the age of four, she went on to master the dance form in every possible way, having over 50 years of dancing experience. Over the years, dance has taken her all over the world and brought her many awards, including the Padma Bhushan, Sangeet Natak Akademi Award, the Padma Vibhushan among others. Saarang 2014 gives to all dance lovers a chance to witness this great maestro at work, right here at Chennai. 

Choreo Night:

Choreo Night being the biggest inter-collegiate group dance competition in South India, is a platform for the nation's best dance crews to show their moves. Watch them set the stage ablaze in a night of mind blowing entertainment and immense fun. The proceeds from this night will go to charity. Be there to experience one of the best performances of your life and support the cause.
